This paper deals with the design of a resource allocation scheme for 5G systems, which involves the use of machine learning algorithms to learn the correlations between various system parameters. The paper also discusses the use of a cloud radio access network (CRAN) architecture to reduce system overhead. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Other likely sub-categories include cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these sub-categories are also relevant to the topics discussed in the paper.
